      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ci): increase timeouts in flaky process-group signal test",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nThe `checks-node-core-tooling` CI job fails intermittently due to a flaky test:\n\n`test/scripts/openclaw-cross-os-release-checks.test.ts` > \"forwards external termination to command process groups\"\n\nThe test fails with `Error: process still alive: <pid>` because the child process doesn't die within the 2s `waitForDead` timeout. This is a timing-sensitive process-group signal forwarding test that fails on heavily loaded CI runners.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe test's signal cascade (SIGTERM -> wait -> SIGKILL to process group) uses very tight timeouts:\n- `OPENCLAW_CROSS_OS_PROCESS_TREE_KILL_AFTER_MS`: 25ms before SIGKILL\n- `waitForDead` timeout: 2000ms for child to die\n\nOn loaded CI runners with many parallel jobs, process creation and signal delivery can be delayed enough that the 25ms kill delay expires before the SIGKILL is delivered, or the 2s wait isn't enough for the child to be reaped.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Increase `OPENCLAW_CROSS_OS_PROCESS_TREE_KILL_AFTER_MS` from 25ms to 200ms (more reliable signal delivery)\n- Increase `waitForDead` timeout from 2000ms to 10000ms (more tolerant of slow CI)\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Stress test (50 iterations, original 25ms timeout)\n\nCommand: `node repro-signal-stress.js` (50 iterations with original 25ms kill delay)\n\n```\nResults: 50/50 passed, 0 failures\nAverage death time: 0ms\n```\n\nOn an unloaded developer machine, even the original 25ms timeout works reliably. The flakiness manifests on heavily loaded CI runners where process scheduling is slower.\n\n### Single-run verification (200ms kill delay, 10s wait)\n\nCommand: `node repro-signal-v2.js`\n\n```\nRunner PID: 3082645, Child PID: 3082659\nRunner exited: code=143 signal=null\nSUCCESS: child 3082659 died\n```\n\nThe child process is reliably killed after the force-kill timer fires.\n\n### Before-fix CI failure (from PR #95400)\n\n```\nFAIL   tooling  test/scripts/openclaw-cross-os-release-checks.test.ts > scripts/openclaw-cross-os-release-checks > forwards external termination to command process groups\nError: process still alive: 9031\n  ❯ waitForDead test/scripts/openclaw-cross-os-release-checks.test.ts:130:9\n```\n\nThe child process (PID 9031) survived past the 2s `waitForDead` timeout on the CI runner.\n\n## What Changed\n\nOnly two test timeout literals in `test/scripts/openclaw-cross-os-release-checks.test.ts`:\n- Line 1283: `OPENCLAW_CROSS_OS_PROCESS_TREE_KILL_AFTER_MS`: `\"25\"` -> `\"200\"`\n- Line 1297: `waitForDead(childPid, 2_000)` -> `waitForDead(childPid, 10_000)`\n\nNo production code changes. No changes to signal handling logic or process management.\n",
        "branch": "fix/flaky-cross-os-signal-test",
